== Appendix C — Scaling to N=28 (Paper Regime)

To reproduce the full paper results, change `N=8` to `N=28` in the hyperparameters cell.

#align(center)[
  #table(
    columns: 4,
    table.header([*Quantity*], [*$N=8$*], [*$N=12$*], [*$N=28$*]),
    [Hilbert space $2^N$], [256], [4096], [$2.7 times 10^8$],
    [Hidden units $M = 3N$], [24], [36], [84],
    [Parameters], [224], [480], [2464],
    [QFM matrix], [$224 times 224$], [$480 times 480$], [$2464 times 2464$],
    [Symmetry kink $N(N+1)/2$], [36], [78], [406],
    [Epochs (used)], [300], [1000], [2000+],
    [Parallel tempering chains], [16], [16], [16],
    [Runtime], [$tilde 10$ min], [$tilde 1.5$ hours], [$tilde$ hours]
  )
]

Additional requirement for N=28: *parallel tempering is mandatory* for the ferromagnetic phases. Exact enumeration for QFM is not feasible; only PT-collected samples can be used.

